<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-20T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1088" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1088">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">890E.00/235: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-20T07:00:00+02:00">November
                                    20, 1943—7 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 7:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2128. My voluntary comment on London’s 8050, November 18, 7 p.m.,
                            repeated here is that the expedient apparently under consideration is
                            immoral in concept and pernicious in effect.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>